no-restricted-syntax.message: Do not import default or named exports from React. Use a namespace import (import * as React from 'react';) instead.
Do not import default or named exports from ReactDOM. Use a namespace import (import * as ReactDOM from 'react-dom';) instead.
Do not import default or named exports from ReactDOM. Use a namespace import (import * as ReactDOM from 'react-dom/client';) instead.
Do not import default or named exports from ReactDOMServer. Use a namespace import (import * as ReactDOM from 'react-dom/server';) instead.
The 'use client' pragma can't be used with export * in the same module. This is not supported by Next.js.
Do not call `Error(...)` without `new`. Use `new Error(...)` instead.
Use global setTimeout instead of window.setTimeout.
Use global setInterval instead of window.setInterval.
Use global clearTimeout instead of window.clearTimeout.
Use global clearInterval instead of window.clearInterval.

paths.name: @mui/material
paths.message:
Prefer one level nested imports to avoid bundling everything in dev mode or breaking CJS/ESM split.
See https://github.com/mui/material-ui/pull/24147 for the kind of win it can unlock.

paths.name: @mui/material/styles
paths.message: Use `MuiStyles<ClassKey, Props>` instead if the styles are exported. Otherwise use `as const` assertions. `createStyles` will lead to inlined, at-compile-time-resolved type-imports. See https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/36097#issuecomment-578324386 for more information
